# Playtest notes / backlog

## Done
- [x] enhance weapon "sprites", they cause eyecancer, and they weren't aligned to the actual position ammo is fired from — the viewmodel was drawn 2% right of true screen-center (`cx = w * 0.52 + bobX`) while `RaycasterEngine.fire()`'s tracer/flame-stream have always launched from a fixed, simulation-adjacent point at exact screen-bottom-center; first attempt wrongly moved the tracer to chase the gun's drawn position, but the correct direction is the reverse — the gun is the cosmetic element, so it's the one that should conform to the fixed shot origin. Fixed by recentering the viewmodel (`WEAPON_CENTER_BIAS` 0.52 → 0.5 in `viewmodel.ts`) instead of touching `effects.ts`/`engine.ts`'s tracer origin at all. Every weapon's Canvas-2D silhouette also got a polish pass (dark outline strokes + a bottom-shadow band to match the existing top-highlight, giving flat fills some bevel) while keeping the existing primitive-shape style rather than a full redesign
- [x] enhance soundfx, esp. weapon fire — every weapon's fire sound was previously the same shared `audio.playShoot()` blip; each of the 7 weapons now has its own procedurally-synthesized voice dispatched off `weapon.viewKind` (`src/engine/audio.ts`): pistol keeps the original snap, shotgun layers a distorted thump with a filtered noise burst, gdb gets a cheap high-pitched tick, ghidra gets a rising launch whoosh (distinct from its existing impact boom), Friday Hotfix gets a continuously-blended rumble+hiss jet, the knife/Toolchain get an airy whoosh / gritty revving buzz respectively — gdb/Friday Hotfix/Toolchain's rapid auto-fire retriggers add a small `Math.random()` pitch jitter so a burst doesn't sound clone-stamped
- [x] flamethrower must burn 2.5x gas considering its dmg — Friday Hotfix's `ammoPerShot` raised from `1` to `2.5` (`src/engine/weapons.ts`), same flat cost every other weapon pays otherwise; HUD's gas readout now floors the value (`src/engine/hud.ts`) since the pool can land on a half-unit
- [x] antialiasing for wall edges — the top/bottom silhouette against ceiling/floor is now sub-pixel blended per column instead of floored to whole pixels (which caused the classic raycaster "staircase" jaggies), by proportionally alpha-blending the one boundary row at each edge with whatever's already painted underneath (`renderScene` in `src/engine/raycaster.ts`); zBuffer/sprite-occlusion resolution is untouched; verified headlessly by bundling `raycaster.ts` and rendering a synthetic wall in Playwright/Chromium, confirming the boundary pixel is a proportional blend of wall and background color [Task 71]
- [x] console hints keep coming when game is paused, spamming away previous output — engine now fires an `onFreezeChange` edge event on the paused/lore-frozen ↔ running transition, which the console sidebar uses to suspend its ambient hint timer while frozen (resumes once unpaused)
- [x] "Suggested repos" section at GitHub loading — four quick-pick buttons (Easy: FizzBuzzEnterpriseEdition, Medium: DOOM, Hard: webpack, Nightmare: magento2) below the repo input fill it in and load immediately, sharing the existing fetch-and-launch flow
- [x] Progress indicator for github loads — the recursive tree fetch (the one genuinely slow step for a big repo) now streams and shows a running "X MB received" counter, and the "Scanning file tree…" fallback pass (each extensionless file costs a real network round-trip) shows a "(checked/total)" counter, instead of one static message
- [x] Highscore table dialog wordwrapped every column — widened dialog (640px→960px) and made only the long-text columns (Campaign, Ended On) wrap; # / Score / Lines / Complexity / Levels / Hash / Replay stay on one line now
