- [x] where is the "continue run" button? never seen it — found a real, pre-existing bug while verifying the rename above: the button's on-load visibility check (`if (loadCampaignSave()) continueButton.style.display = "";`) runs at module top-level *before* `const SAVE_KEY` was declared further down the file — the same shape of bug as the `GORE_KEY` one from Task 30. `loadCampaignSave` is a hoisted function so the call itself doesn't error, but the instant it reads `SAVE_KEY` it hits the const's temporal dead zone, throws, and the function's own empty `catch` silently swallows it, always returning `null` — so the button never auto-showed on load, for any save, regardless of validity (the *other* call site, inside the button's own click handler, runs after full module init and always worked fine, which is presumably why this went unnoticed). Fixed the same way `GORE_KEY` was: moved `SAVE_KEY`'s declaration up next to `GORE_KEY`/`DIFFICULTY_KEY`/the volume keys, with the same explanatory comment. Verified against the real built app in headless Chromium: reproduced the bug against the pristine pre-fix code first (button stayed hidden even with a valid save seeded into `localStorage`), then confirmed the fix flips it to shown on load; a page with no save correctly still stays hidden [Task 48]. Follow-up: the now-visible button had no dedicated CSS at all and fell back to a bare default `<button>` — small, gray, left-aligned next to the full-width red Select Workspace button. First pass gave it matching full-width/padding/radius but a muted secondary color so it wouldn't compete with the primary CTA. Second follow-up, per explicit request: Select Workspace/Continue Run/Load from GitHub are three different ways to start the same game loop, so they're now grouped into a tab strip (Local/Continue/GitHub) with only the active one's panel shown — the Continue tab itself is hidden entirely (not just disabled) when no save exists, same visibility condition as before, and switch