- [x] unlockable flamethrower, cone aoe, called "Friday Hotfix". Same drop/unlock mechanics as the existing ones. forced unlock at level 12. Uses dedicated ammo "Gas", to be dropped like other ammo — added as a sixth `WEAPONS` entry (`weapons.ts`): fully automatic, 6 pellets in a 100px-wide cone (nearly 1.5x the shotgun's 70px, the widest in the arsenal), so it melts anything at point-blank range but the spread scatters wide of a target well before `FOG_FAR`, giving it a flamethrower's short effective range without a dedicated max-range mechanic. Drew its own `"gas"` `AmmoType`/`LootKind` pool rather than repeating gdb's original shared-bullets mistake (see the `smg` split in Task 57) — its own HUD readout ("GAS", fiery orange), starting reserve (`STARTING_GAS_AMMO = 40`), drop size (`GAS_DROP_AMOUNT = 30`, magazine-sized like `SMG_DROP_AMOUNT`), and elite-already-owned top-up (`ELITE_GAS_DROP_AMOUNT = 80`). `FRIDAY_HOTFIX_WEAPON_INDEX` added alongside `GDB_WEAPON_INDEX`/`GHIDRA_WEAPON_INDEX` and folded into `UNLOCKABLE_WEAPONS`, so the existing Elite-kill guaranteed-drop and secret-room weapon-unlock loot slot (`placeSecretRooms`, already generic over an opaque `missingWeaponIndices` list) picked it up with no map-layer changes at all. `main.ts`'s `FORCED_UNLOCK_LEVELS` gained a `{ level: 12, weaponIndex: FRIDAY_HOTFIX_WEAPON_INDEX }` entry. Threaded `gas` through the full ammo lifecycle the same way `bullets`/`rockets`/`smg` already were: `EngineStats`/`EngineCarryover`, `fire()`'s ammo check/deduction (factored the growing bullets/rockets/smg/gas ternary chain into a small `ammoPool()` helper rather than nesting a fourth level), the IDKFA cheat, `CampaignSave`/`loadCampaignSave` (defaults missing `gas` to 0 for older saves), `rollLoot`'s new `hasFridayHotfix` gate (excludes `"gas"` from the loot table entirely until owned, mirroring `hasGdb`/`hasRocketLauncher`), and `computeScore`'s ammo-remaining bonus (now a four-way average across bullets/rockets/smg/gas inst