- [x] elite enemies should have not only their usual loot, but also drop a still locked weapon additionally (two drops) with a chance of 60% — reworked `dropEliteLoot` (`engine.ts`): the health-or-ammo drop used to be an either/or fallback only rolled when the weapon-drop branch *didn't* fire; it's now always rolled first, unconditionally. A separate, independent roll then decides whether to *additionally* push a second "weapon" drop at the same position, via `rollBonusWeaponDrop` (`loot.ts`, generalized from Task 74's normal-kill version to take an explicit `chance` parameter, defaulting to the normal-kill rate) at a new `ELITE_BONUS_WEAPON_DROP_CHANCE = 0.6`. Net effect: an Elite now leaves two items on the ground most of the time a weapon's still missing, not a choice between them. Updated every doc/comment describing the old "guaranteed weapon drop" framing (`weapons.ts`'s `STARTING_WEAPONS`/`UNLOCKABLE_WEAPONS`/arsenal doc comments, `engine.ts`'s `ownedWeapons` field comment, `doc/user/mechanics.md`'s Elite row and Loot & Difficulty bullets, `doc/dev/game-design.md`'s Elite description, `doc/dev/decisions.md`'s Ammo/Loot Gating section) to "high-odds bonus drop" instead. Follow-up: user flagged the "still-unlocked weapon" wording in the docs/comments as backwards (a weapon you don't have yet is *locked*, not *unlocked*) — corrected to "still-locked" everywhere it appeared (`loot.ts`, `doc/user/mechanics.md`, `doc/dev/decisions.md`); `engine.ts`'s existing "still-unowned" phrasing was already correct and left alone. Verified with a Node+esbuild harness bundling the real `loot.ts` against the actual `mulberry32` seeded PRNG this game uses for every sim-relevant roll (not a toy RNG): confirmed `ELITE_BONUS_WEAPON_DROP_CHANCE` is 0.6, the default (no explicit chance arg) still resolves to the 1% normal-kill rate, an explicit elite-chance roll that would miss at 1% correctly hits at 60%, and a 500k-trial statistical check landed within 0.08% of the intended 60% hit 